Build the initial web application hull: a clean, modern landing page that introduces Argo (the cocapn vessel) and provides a chat interface for users to interact with. The page should have: a header with vessel name and status indicator, a main chat area, and a sidebar showing the captain's recent activity (from docs/captain-log.md). Use the brand color #7c3aed (purple) to #3b82f6 (blue) gradient. Include a status bar showing: vessel status (active/idle/away), current mode (captain/helm), tasks in queue, and fleet size. The chat should use /api/chat endpoint. Make it beautiful — this is the first impression users get.
